{
  "stem": "1061.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were not religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "However, they had a very strong Jewish identity.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this is how my mother was so involved with the Zionist movement, because that was their way of-- of reaffirming what they considered themselves to be.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in fact, I went after my regular school-- excuse me-- I went to a Hebrew afternoon school, which was a secular school, you see, to learn the language and to study the poems of [INAUDIBLE] and such.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was very interesting because it was just one more language to learn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and of course, that ended with the war, as my education, my formal Polish education, ended because the Jewish children were not allowed to participate in schools.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, there's always a way to manage, otherwise.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I have a frog in my throat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anyhow, what happened is because my oldest sister had all of the books at home, and we children were really not allowed in the streets for the reason that the Germans who-- the gestapo were always around with dogs.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was just absolute, total terror for a child to be outside and see these-- these marching-- you know, the German-- the gestapo with the dogs, they sort of had a-- they-- they had a certain posture.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And just looking at it was frightening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what we did is-- I'll take a little water.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[DRINKS] We stayed home and my oldest sister, Anna, organized little classes, you see.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, whatever books were in the house, and there were plenty of those, including manuals, because she had all her school books.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we learned-- I learned Latin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I learned French.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I learned chemistry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I wasn't even out of elementary school yet.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
